The list of top 5 water tank brands in Kenya will make your search easier if you are looking for a reliable tank supplier. This is because you need to be wary to not buy tanks from a fly by night suppliers who is here today and gone tomorrow. The reason for this is that you want to buy a tank that will last for years to come. I can testify to the fact that if you buy wisely the tank will keep going and going. A tank that I have has lasted for over 20 year and it still remains robust and leak-free. That is what I call a good buy. In Kenya the vast majority of water tank brands are made from food grade polyethylene material. But what does food grade mean? Well it can be better referred to as a food safe plastic material or in this case water safe plastic material. This means that foods that acidic foods that can leach chemicals from the container they are in will not do so giving you water that will be safe and free of any strange taste. Also read: Prices of Water Tanks in Kenya All the most popular plastic water tank brands in Kenya are  rotationally moulded water tanks. When shopping look for a brand that assures you of a double layered tank for better durability. Some of the brands will boast of 100% virgin food grade plastic this means that the plastic used has not been recycled. The virgin plastic will have better mechanical properties ensuring a longer lifespan than recycled plastic. A tank that has been UV stabilized will mean that it will be protected from UV light degradation which is another plus. So lets now take a look at the top 5 water tank brands in Kenya starting from the oldest established brand.  Brand Name    